This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the problem of textual relation embedding and relation extraction. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a method to improve the performance of existing relation extraction models. Additionally, it involves the use of statistical methods and machine learning techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the problem of extracting relational facts from text.
